commitResults.messageTitle: Fix remaining test issues and code issues found from testing
commitResults.messageBody:
- Fix `equals` not handling null fields correctly in some classes
- Fix `TypicalPersons` class to match `typicalPersonsAddressBook.json`
- Fix some general code quality issues

- Fix InterviewDate being a required field when it should be optional
- Fix InternshipStatus being optional when it should be a required field
- Fix InternshipRole `equals` method
- Fix incorrect code blocks for null checks in `JsonAdaptedInternship` `toModelType` method
- Fix `Id` fields not updating correctly after loading data from json
    - Create methods for updating the next Id counters correctly in `AddressBook`
    - Fix tests not working with updated id behaviour

- Modify `AddInternshipCommandParser` to now parse an `Index`, which will be used to find the person to link the newly created `Internship` to
    - Modify `CLISyntax` prefixes to match UG and new command format for add internship
    - Modify `AddInternshipCommand` class to support linking via use of `Index`
- Update `AddressBook` methods for add and remove to support 2-way linking
    - Modify `addPerson` such that if the `Person` to add contains a link to some `Internship`, then a link is also established from that `Internship` to this `Person, and vice versa for `addInternship`
    - Modify `removePerson` such that if the `Person` to remove contains a link to some `Internship`, then the link from that `Internship` to this `Person` is also removed, and vice versa for `removeInternship`

commitResults.messageBody:
Link Command will link person at index `PERSON_INDEX` and
internship at `INTERNSHIP_INDEX` together

When provided either `PERSON_INDEX`, `INTERNSHIP_INDEX` or both,
Unlink Command will remove the link between the person and
internship specified.

Exceptions will be thrown if link is not found, or specified
person and internship are found to not be linked to persons or
internships other than each other.

- Updated Link Command Success message to display person and
internship names only rather than all details

commitResults.messageTitle: Add tests for Link Command and Unlink Command
commitResults.messageBody:
Update Command Exceptions for Unlink Command

Command checks for 2 main cases:
1. 1 person/internship is provided
- if provided person/internship has no linked person/internship,
Command will throw an unlinked person/internship error

2. both person and internship are provided
- if either person or internship has no linked person/internship,
Command will throw an unlinked person/internship error
- if both person and internship provided is linked, but do not link
to each other, Command will throw an incorrect linked
person/internship error

Note: if both person and internship provided is incorrect (either
due to incorrect or absense of link) The person error will be thrown
first
